Preheat your oven to 220°C. Halve the @yellow pepper{1} and discard the core and
seeds. Slice into thin strips. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}. Peel
and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).
Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1} in a #sieve{}. Pop the pepper on a
#baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and
@pepper{pinch}. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until charred and really
soft, about ~{15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once
hot, add the onion and fry until golden and soft, stirring occasionally,
~{5-6%minutes}. Add the @Central American style spice mix{1} and half the
garlic, stir and cook for ~{1%minute} then pour in the @finely chopped tomatoes{1}(canned), mixed beans, a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a pinch of
@sugar{pinch}. Stir in the @vegetable stock powder{1} and pour in the water
(see ingredients for amount).

Bring the mixture to the boil, reduce the heat to medium-high and simmer until
the sauce has thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}. Add a splash of water if the mixture
is looking a little dry. While the mixture simmers, halve, peel and thinly slice
the @echalion shallot{1}. Trim the @green beans{150%g}. Break the
@feta cheese{50%g} up into small pieces.

Mix the roasted pepper into the bean mixture, then pour into a rectangular
#ovenproof dish{}. Unroll the @puff pastry sheet{1/2} and cover the filling.

> TIP: It doesn't matter if the pastry sits just on top of the mixture or goes
> over the edge of the dish, it will depend on the size of your dish!

Make a small hole in the middle of the pastry. Bake on the top shelf of your
oven until the pastry is puffed and golden, about ~{15-20%minutes}.

Wash out your frying pan, pop back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.
When hot, add the green beans and a pinch of salt and pepper. Stir-fry until
starting to char, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add in the shallot and stir-fry until golden
and soft, ~{4%minutes}. Add the remaining garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.
Add a splash of water, cover the pan with a #lid{} or some #foil{}, allow the
beans to steam until tender, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from the heat and set aside.

Stir the feta through the green beans (keep some plain if some people don't
like the feta!). Serve the pie on plates with the garlicky green beans
alongside. Enjoy!